        <sect1>
            <title>Techniques</title>

            <para>
                <e>Techniques</e> are a special form of advantages which may
                always be purchased after character generation. Each technique
                is tied to one or more skills, and represents a special usage
                of that skill.
            </para>

            <para>
                A technique has a cost associated with it, and may only be
                purchased once the level of the skill is equal to the cost
                of the technique. If a technique is associated with several
                skills, then as long as one skill has reached the desired
                level, then the technique may be purchased. However, the
                technique can only be used with those skills which are of
                sufficient level. As soon as a lower level skill is raised to
                the required level, then the technique may be used with it
                at no extra cost.
            </para>

            <para>
                If a technique has a cost of zero, then it is automatically
                known as soon as the character has a skill of at least one,
                at no cost.
            </para>

